Description: ultra-fast cross-platform screenshot library for Python
 MSS (Multiple ScreenShots) is a pure-Python ctypes library that captures
 screenshots at maximum speed without any external dependencies. On Linux
 it accesses X11 and XRandR directly via ctypes; no PIL or OpenCV is
 required for capture.
 .
 Optional Pillow integration converts raw pixel buffers to PNG or other
 image formats. Useful for game recording tools, automated QA harnesses,
 and screen-capture overlays.
 .
 Also ships the mss(1) command-line tool for one-shot screenshot capture.
